# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000239> (brush border epithelial cell)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000239> "An epithelial cell characterized by the presence of a brush border on its apical surface, which increases the surface area for absorption.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000239> <https://doi.org/10.1152/ajpgi.00005.2011>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000239> "PMID:25422372")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000239> "All brush border cells are columnar-cuboidal.  The formal logical definition of this term asserts this. Brush border epithelial cells are predominantly found lining the small intestine and the proximal tubules of the kidneys.")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000239> "brush border epithelial cell")
EquivalentClasses(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000239> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000066> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0005903>)))
