AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000969> "regulatory B-lymphocyte")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000969> "Regulatory B cells reportedly represent 1-2% of the spleen and 7-8% of the peritoneal B220-positive cells in mice. They are also found in the bone marrow, lymph node, and blood of mice. These cells are also reportedly capable of secreting IL-10 and are reportedly CD5-positive, CD21-positive, CD24-positive, CD93-negative, B220-positive, IgM-positive, and IgD-positive.")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0000969> "regulatory B cell")
