# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0002377> (immature Schwann cell)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "GOC:cvs") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "GOC:tfm") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "ISBN:0721662544") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0002377> "A glial cell that develops from a Schwann cell precursor. The immature Schwann cell is embedded among neurons (axons) with minimal extracellular spaces separating them from nerve cell membranes and has a basal lamina. Cells can survive without an axon present. Immature Schwann cell can be found communally ensheathing large groups of axons.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0002377> <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1980-3228>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#creation_date> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0002377> "2010-09-24T02:10:31Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
