# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0002401> (mature dendritic epithelial T cell precursor)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "GOC:tfm") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "http://www.immgen.org/index_content.html") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0002401> "A thymocyte that has a T cell receptor consisting of a gamma chain that has as part a Vgamma3 segment, and a delta chain. This cell type is CD4-negative, CD8-negative and CD24-negative. This cell-type is found in the fetal thymus with highest numbers occurring at E17-E18.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0002401> <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1980-3228>)
