# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0020031> (CD8-positive exhausted alpha-beta T cell)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "PMID:31207603") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "PMID:36907685") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "PMID:38166256") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0020031> "A CD8-positive alpha-beta T cell that displays impaired function and altered differentiation as a result of chronic antigenic stimulation (e.g., chronic infection, tumours, or persistent inflammation). This state is characterised by sustained expression of PD-1 as a shared feature. Additional exhaustion-associated molecules, including expression of the transcription factor TOX and reduced T-bet, and context- or stage-dependent changes in markers such as LAG-3, TIM-3, CD39, and EOMES, may also be observed; however, the expression levels of these molecules vary depending on exhaustion stage and disease context.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0020031> <https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5742-4697>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_0020031> <https://orcid.org/0009-0000-8480-9277>)
