# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_4072103> (hair follicle dermal stem cell)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "PMID:25465495") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "PMID:29691589") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "PMID:35036581") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "PMID:35069694") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_4072103> "A bipotent mesenchymal stem cell that resides in the dermal sheath, specifically within the dermal sheath cup at the base of the hair follicle, characterized by its capacity for self-renewal and differentiation into both dermal sheath and dermal papilla cells throughout hair cycling. In humans, this cell is marked by enriched expression of gremlin-2 (GREM2) and dipeptidase-1 (DPEP1), and acts as a progenitor reservoir sustaining and regenerating the follicle's mesenchymal compartments.")
